<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	A recent report by the Department of Health and Ageing (2008) indicated that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent report (Department of Health and Ageing, 2008) showed that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
When the author is referred to more than once in the same paragraph, do not include the date in 
subsequent references, as long as the study cannot be confused with others cited. If you provide the 
abbreviation the first time you can use it instead of the full name subsequently.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In a recent report the Department of Health and Ageing (DEHA) (2008) showed&hellip; DEHA also reported&hellip;
</blockquote>
